    <text id="A7515T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Sibert thanks Evans for gifts which she believes he has been anonymously sending
                    to her.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1866-09-27">Sept. 27, /'66.</date>
                        <name type="place">Cottage by the Lake</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Mr. D.H. Evans,</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>Some unknown, but very kind friend has been thoughtfully sending me the "Ledger"
                    since my return from Staunton. I once thought it was Mr. <unclear>Jn</unclear>
                    Ryan but remembered he only sent me papers containing some communication written
                    by himself. I've at last concluded it must be you. If so, I sincerely thank you.
                    Truly do I appreciate such evidence of your esteemed remembrance. And most
                    earnestly do I<pb n="2"/>wish that the power were mine to repay your kindness.
                    perhaps that pleasure will yet be mine. I hope so from my heart. I may some day
                    meet with the one you love best. Then will be one of my opportunities to
                    compensate. With deep &amp; sincere respect &amp; wishing that your
                    future may be ever prosperous, &amp; happy I am</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Truly Your friend</salute>
                    <signed>Mary A. Sibert</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
